paragraphs.title: expr Function
paragraphs.text:
c = ['c_customer_sk', 'c_birth_day', 'c_birth_year', 'c_birth_country', 'c_last_review_date', 'c_birth_month']
df = customer.select(c)

cond = """case when c_birth_month > 9 then 'Q4'
            else case when c_birth_month > 6 then 'Q3'
                else case when c_birth_month > 3 then 'Q2'
                    else case when c_birth_month > 0 then 'Q1'
                        end
                    end
                end
            end as birth_quarter"""
            
newdf = df.withColumn("birth_quarter", expr(cond))
z.show(newdf)

paragraphs.title: selectExpr
paragraphs.text:
cond = """case when c_birth_month > 9 then 'Q4'
            else case when c_birth_month > 6 then 'Q3'
                else case when c_birth_month > 3 then 'Q2'
                    else case when c_birth_month > 0 then 'Q1'
                        end
                    end
                end
            end as Quarter"""
            
customer.select(c).selectExpr("*", cond).show()

# how – ‘any’ or ‘all’. If ‘any’, drop a row if it contains any nulls. If ‘all’, drop a row only if all its values are null.
